olive oil
1 packet couscous
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
¾ cup boiling water
1 packet green beans
1 courgette
2 clove garlic
2 packet salmon
drizzle white wine vinegar
1 packet parsley
½ packet Dill & Parsley Mayonnaise

• Boil the kettle. Place couscous and chicken-style stock powder in a medium heatproof bowl.
• Add the boiling water (3/4 cup for 2 people / 11/2 cups for 4 people) and stir to combine.
• Immediately cover with a plate and leave until all water is absorbed, 5 minutes. Fluff up with a fork and set aside.

• Meanwhile, trim and halve green beans. Slice courgette into half-moons. Finely chop garlic.
• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook green beans and courgette until tender, 4-6 minutes.
• Add garlic and cook until fragrant, 1 minute. Transfer to bowl with couscous.

• Return frying pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Pat salmon dry with paper towel and season generously on both sides.
• When oil is hot, cook salmon, skin-side down first, until just cooked through, 2-4 minutes each side (cook in batches for best results).
TIP: Patting the skin dry helps it crisp up in the pan!

• To bowl with the couscous, add a drizzle of white wine vinegar and stir to combine. Season to taste.
• Divide super green couscous between bowls. Top with salmon.
• Drizzle over dill & parsley mayonnaise and tear over parsley to serve. Enjoy!